  "prompt": "What's the one song that can fix any bad mood?",
  "response": "There's no single song that universally fixes a bad mood for everyone, as musical preferences are highly subjective. However, some songs are often cited for their uplifting and feel-good qualities. Here are a few popular choices that might help brighten your day:\n\n1. \"Happy\" by Pharrell Williams\n2. \"Don't Stop Believin'\" by Journey\n3. \"Walking on Sunshine\" by Katrina and the Waves\n4. \"Uptown Funk\" by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars\n5. \"Shake It Off\" by Taylor Swift\n\nUltimately, the best song to lift your spirits is one that resonates personally with you and brings back positive memories or feelings.",
